      • access

        public java.lang.Integer access(int address)
        Method that calculates the LRU stack distance for a particular address. If the address has never been accessed before, then its LRU stack distance is infinity.
        Parameters:
        address - The address being accessed
        Returns:
        Integer representing the calculated stack distance, null is returned if the distance is infinity.
